{"name": "co2monitor", "metadata": {"name": "co2monitor", "version": "0.2.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License (GPL)"], "home_page": null, "license": "GPL-3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["click", "loguru", "python-dotenv", "requests"], "summary": "See the current co2 emissions per kWh of electricity in the Netherlands", "upload_time": 1732892296}, "documentation": ["\n# Table of Contents\n\n1.  [CO2 monitor](#org5a19499)\n2.  [Install](#orgc2c30e5)\n    1.  [Development](#org989c74b)\n3.  [Pins](#orgf82dd73)\n    1.  [Screen](#org75b8d64)\n\n\n\n<a id=\"org5a19499\"></a>\n\n# CO2 monitor\n\nThis project is more or less like [co2monitor.nl](https://co2monitor.nl), except that we show the current CO2 emisions per kWh of electricity on a small EPD screen, connected to some GPIO pins of a Raspberry Pi.\n\nSee [Pins](#orgf82dd73) for an overview of what pins need to be connected to the screen.\n\n\n<a id=\"orgc2c30e5\"></a>\n\n# Install\n\n1.  Attach your EPD screen to the pins as described in the table in [Screen](#org75b8d64).\n2.  Install the python executable: `uv sync`, or `pip install -e .`\n3.  Copy [.env.example](.env.example) to [.env](.env) and populate with the correct api key. You can find an api key on\n    <https://ned.nl/nl/user>\n4.  Run the executable (found in the virtualenv/bin directory).\n\n\n<a id=\"org989c74b\"></a>\n\n## Development\n\nSee the [Makefile](Makefile) for handy dev commands. I use [uv](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv) to manage my dependencies, but it does not really matter all that much.\n\nYou can execute `python monitor` (or `uv run python monitor`) to quickly run the project.\n\n\n<a id=\"orgf82dd73\"></a>\n\n# Pins\n\n<https://pinout.xyz/>\n\n\n<a id=\"org75b8d64\"></a>\n\n## Screen\n\n[Product](https://www.waveshare.com/product/displays/e-paper/2.9inch-e-paper-module-b.htm)\n\n<table border=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"6\" rules=\"groups\" frame=\"hsides\">\n\n\n<colgroup>\n<col  class=\"org-left\" />\n\n<col  class=\"org-left\" />\n\n<col  class=\"org-left\" />\n\n<col  class=\"org-right\" />\n\n<col  class=\"org-left\" />\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th scope=\"col\" class=\"org-left\">Name</th>\n<th scope=\"col\" class=\"org-left\">Function</th>\n<th scope=\"col\" class=\"org-left\">Color</th>\n<th scope=\"col\" class=\"org-right\">Pin number</th>\n<th scope=\"col\" class=\"org-left\">GPIO</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"org-left\">VCC</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Power</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Grey</td>\n<td class=\"org-right\">1</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">-</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td class=\"org-left\">GND</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Ground</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Brown</td>\n<td class=\"org-right\">6</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">-</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td class=\"org-left\">DIN</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">SPI MOSI</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Blue</td>\n<td class=\"org-right\">19</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">10 (SPI0 MOSI)</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td class=\"org-left\">CLK</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">SPI Clock</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Yellow</td>\n<td class=\"org-right\">23</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">11 (SPI0 SCLK)</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td class=\"org-left\">CS</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">SPI chip selection</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Orange</td>\n<td class=\"org-right\">24</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">8  (SPI0 CE0)</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td class=\"org-left\">DC</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Data/Command selection</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Green</td>\n<td class=\"org-right\">22</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">25</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td class=\"org-left\">RST</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Reset</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">White</td>\n<td class=\"org-right\">11</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">17</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td class=\"org-left\">BUSY</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Busy status output</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">Purple</td>\n<td class=\"org-right\">18</td>\n<td class=\"org-left\">24</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "monitor.cliprinter", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "monitor.cliprinter.CliPrinter", "bases": ["Handler"], "methods": [{"name": "monitor.cliprinter.CliPrinter.handle", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": {"name": "EnergyData", "xref": {"fqname": "monitor.api.EnergyData", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "monitor.main", "documentation": ["!/home/rens/.virtualenvs/monitor/bin/python"], "functions": [{"name": "monitor.main.app", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ctx", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "debug", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "api_key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "api_url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "user_agent", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "polltime", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "monitor.main.default_handler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "handler", "type": {"name": "Type", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Handler", "xref": {"fqname": "monitor.handler.Handler", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "monitor.main.cli", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "monitor.main.screen", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "monitor.main.tray", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ctx", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "monitor.main.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "opts", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"f